RESTful API for the future shatag server:

$URL is the service endpoint, https://example.com/shatag

send a bunch of hashes:

PUT $URL/host/<hostname>
Data: json document containing { hash => path, hash => path, ...}

check if a hash exists:

GET $URL/where/<hash>
Data: list of hosts

GET $URL/find/<hash>
Data: document containing { host => path, host => path, ...}
